{{Taxobox | name = | image = Arapaima leptosoma 2009 G2.jpg | image2 = Arapaima leptosoma 2009 G1.jpg | image2_caption = ''Arapaima leptosoma'' in [[Sevastopol Zoo]]-Aquarium | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Chordate|Chordata]] | classis = [[Actinopterygii]] | ordo = [[Osteoglossiformes]] | familia = [[Arapaimidae]] | genus = ''[[Arapaima (genus)|Arapaima]]'' | species = '''''A. leptosoma''''' | binomial = ''Arapaima leptosoma'' | binomial_authority = [[Donald J. Stewart|Stewart]], 2013<ref name=description>Stewart D. J. (2013). [http://www.asihcopeiaonline.org/doi/abs/10.1643/CI-12-017 "A New Species of ''Arapaima'' (Osteoglossomorpha: Osteoglossidae) from the Solimões River, Amazonas State, Brazil"]. ''[[Copeia]]'' '''2013'''(3); 470-476.</ref> }}
'''''Arapaima leptosoma''''' is a [[species]] of freshwater fish [[endemism|endemic]] to near the confluence of the [[Solimões]] and [[Purus River]]s in [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]], Brazil.<ref name=practical>[http://www.practicalfishkeeping.co.uk/content.php?sid=95 Practicalfishkeeping.co.uk]</ref> Like other members of the [[genus]] ''[[Arapaima (genus)|Arapaima]]'', this fish can breathe air.<ref name=scinews>[http://www.sci-news.com/biology/science-giant-fish-arapaima-brazil-01455.html Sci-news.com]</ref> It has a deep caudal peduncle relative to other species in its genus.<ref name=description/> It is the first new member of ''Arapaima'' to be described since 1847. Member species of the genus ''Arapaima'' are the largest freshwater fish in South America.<ref name=practical/>
